In this episode, we dive deep into the world of mutants as we review the first 5 episodes of the highly anticipated reboot of the beloved 90s animated series, X-Men '97. Join us as we journey back to Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters and reunite with our favorite mutants - Wolverine, Storm, Cyclops, Jean Grey, and many more.

We'll explore how the show's creators have modernized the animation while staying true to the essence of the original series, capturing the hearts of both longtime fans and a new generation of viewers. From the iconic theme song to the intricate storylines, we'll discuss how X-Men '97 manages to balance nostalgia with fresh, contemporary storytelling. Grab your visor and sharpen your claws, as we do a deep dive into the first 5 episodes of X-Men '97!

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

